frameDefinitions: An Executive_authority exercises their power to reduce or remove negative consequences for someone who has been labeled an Offender who participated in an Crime.
These adjectives describe the degree of strictness or tolerance of an Agent, usually with regard to another person (the Controllee) and often with regard to a particular Issue.
An Authority excuses an Offense that an Offender has committed, with the effect of ending or preventing any punishment.

An Agent restricts the movement of a Theme to within the vicinity of the Holding_location, despite the Theme's desire, plan, or tendency towards motion; the Agent may also use an Instrument.

listRoleDefinitions: The individual who is accused or convicted of a <fen>Crime</fen>.
An action deemed criminal by law.
The constitutionally specified authority who has the power to grant clemency.
The time at which clemency is granted.
The location at which the <fen>Executive_authority</fen> grants clemency.

The Agent is the person who is strict or liberal in his/her control over another. This role is usually the External Argument with predicate adjectives, or the head noun if the adjective is used attributively: <fex name='Agent'>The school</fex> is very <t>liberal</t> in approach and curriculum. I attended a very <t>liberal</t> <fex name='Agent'>school</fex>.

The Agent's strictness may be directed towards or limited to some particular person or group over whom he/she has control.  The Controlled_entity generally occurs in a PP Complement.
Grandparents are often <t>indulgent</t> <fex name='Controlled_entity'>with their grandchildren</fex>.
The Agent's strictness may be manifested in particular behavior: The judge was <t>lenient</t> <fex name='Controlling_act'>in dealing with the offender</fex>.

The Agent may be strict or lenient with respect to a particular matter or situation.  Issue occurs in PP Complements, usually headed by <ment>about</ment>: The city council is <t>strict</t> <fex name='Issue'>about pollution control</fex>.

A Medium of control, such as rules, may also be described as strict or lenient.  Medium may occur with or without the Agent who ultimately has control (i.e. the one who implements or enforces the rules). The club has <t>strict</t> <fex name='Medium'>rules</fex> about who can become a member. <fex name='Medium'>Immigration law</fex> is very <t>strict</t>.
The body part or expression of the <fen>Agent</fen> that indicates their strictness.

The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is the person whose <fen>Behavior</fen> towards other human beings is being evaluated.
The <fen>Affected_party</fen> is the entity which is positively or negatively treated by the <fen>Evaluee</fen>.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> is the action of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> on which the evaluation of the <fen>Evaluee</fen>'s character is based.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the situation or person that the <fen>Evaluee</fen>'s <fen>Behavior</fen> responds to or is related to.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which indicates the character of the <fen>Evaluee</fen>.
The <fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) who carries off and holds the <fen>Victim</fen> against his or her will.
The <fen>Victim</fen> is the person who is carried off and held against his/her will.
When the kidnapping occurs.
Where the kidnapping takes place.
The entity which is confined.
The area within which the <fen>Theme</fen> comes to be confined.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person intentionally restricting the movement of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient entity which is responsible for restricting the movement or location of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
When the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
